Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -e

    echo ">>> Installing Python & pytest"
    apt-get update
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3 \
        python3-pip
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    echo ">>> Preparing dataset directory and files"
    # Create a writable home for the runtime (non-root) user
    mkdir -p /home/user/datasets
    chmod -R 777 /home/user

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # /home/user/datasets/experiment_A.csv
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    cat > /home/user/datasets/experiment_A.csv <<'EOF'
SampleID,Condition,GeneCount,Quality
S1,control,1523,0.98
S2,treated,1480,0.95
S3,control,1601,0.97
S4,treated,1499,0.96
S5,control,1588,0.99
EOF

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # /home/user/datasets/experiment_B.csv
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    cat > /home/user/datasets/experiment_B.csv <<'EOF'
ID,Expression,Dose
S1,0.83,5
S2,0.72,10
S3,0.79,5
S4,0.75,10
S5,0.81,5
EOF

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # /home/user/datasets/notes.tsv  (TAB-separated)
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    cat > /home/user/datasets/notes.tsv <<'EOF'
Run	Date	Operator	Remark
1	2023-03-13	Dr.X	OK
2	2023-03-14	Dr.X	OK
3	2023-03-15	Dr.X	Retry
4	2023-03-16	Dr.X	OK
5	2023-03-17	Dr.X	OK
EOF

    # Ensure everything is world-readable and writable by the running user
    chmod -R a+rw /home/user/datasets

%labels
    chmod 755 /home/user

    Author "Generated by AI – Apptainer setup for life-science data aggregation task"

%help
    Container that provides the initial state for the “combined_dataset” task.
    It includes:
      • Python 3 and pytest for automated testing.
      • Pre-populated source data in /home/user/datasets as required by the task.
      • A writable /home/user so that the learner (non-root) can create results.